metadata.name: The Lost Paradise
metadata.description:
Kawah Ijen is one of East Java‘s hidden gems. With a massive 20-kilometer-wide caldera filled with picturesque turquoise-colored waters, that seem to glimmer even more once touched by sunrise’s golden rays, Ijen is also the world’s largest acidic crater lake. 

Climbing up the ridge overlooking the crater, I was “gifted” with an otherworldly view of a scenery, that at once made me realize how a place so perilous can also be so majestically beautiful.
